LeakMonitor
LeakMonitor is a simple MVP web service that allows users to check if their email address has appeared in known data breaches using the Have I Been Pwned (HIBP) API.
It also extracts and displays the domain part of the email for potential future domain-level monitoring.

🚀 Features
Check if an email has appeared in known breaches.

Display a list of breaches with names and dates (if found).

Extract and display the domain from the email.

Frontend validation of email format.

Loading spinner during checks.

⚙ Tech Stack
Node.js + Express

Axios (API requests)

Vanilla JS + HTML + CSS

dotenv (secure API key management)

🛠 Installation
1️⃣ Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/leakmonitor.git
cd leakmonitor

2️⃣ Install dependencies:
npm install

3️⃣ Create a .env file in the root directory and fill it like this:
HIBP_API_KEY=your_hibp_api_key
PORT=3000

4️⃣ Run the app:
node server.js

🌐 Usage
Open http://localhost:3000

Enter a valid email address

View breach status and domain info

📝 Notes
Requires a valid HIBP API key (free or paid depending on usage level).

MVP focuses on email checks; future versions may include domain-level and phone number checks.

💡 Future Roadmap
User registration and saved checks

Email notifications for breach updates

API for companies to monitor domains

Localization (multi-language support)

🛡 Disclaimer
LeakMonitor does not store or share your email addresses or results.
All checks are done in real-time via HIBP API.

